.TH M3UTOLOCAL 1 "February 2026" "m3utolocal 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
m3utolocal \- Download files from an M3U file based on search query
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B m3utolocal
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fIQUERY\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B m3utolocal
is a command-line tool that searches for channels in an M3U playlist file and downloads the associated files. It filters out live streams by checking file extensions and provides an interactive TUI selection menu to choose specific matches. It also features a granular, color-coded progress bar during downloads.
.PP
The tool validates file sizes before downloading. If a local file already exists and its size matches the remote file, the download is skipped. If the sizes differ, the file is redownloaded.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.I QUERY
Search query to match against \fBtvg-id\fR or \fBtvg-name\fR attributes in the M3U file.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-m ", " \-\-m3u " \fIFILE\fR"
Path to the M3U file (default: \fIchans.m3u\fR).
.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-\-threads " \fIN\fR"
Number of simultaneous downloads (default: 1).
.TP
.BR \-y ", " \-\-yes
Bypass the interactive TUI selection and download all matches automatically.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show the help message and exit.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I downloads/
Directory where downloaded files are stored.
